ain_2532701\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uir1665702875362.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uir1665702875362.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uir1665702875362.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uir1665702875362\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Packing Codes for Unicode\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"uir1665702875362__packing_codes_for_unicode_93004\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, the <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> packing code is for Unicode characters. The <code class=\"ph codeph\">U*</code> packing code can also be used for holding Unicode characters. If the entity character set is Unicode, the <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> packing code can also be used for Unicode characters.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28379e1_d28380e1_d28381e1\">Fields with data type String can be used for Unicode. If a string field is a Unifield, it can hold bold, italic, and underline characters.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uir1665702875362__topic_d18947e1_d18948e1_d18949e1_d18950e1_d18951e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355214e65\">\n                        \n W Packing Code\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28385e1_d28386e1_d28387e1\">By default, if a string field uses the <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> packing code, it can contain any Unicode character. However, some databases support only Unicode BMP (Basic Multilingual Plane ), or do not support Unicode at all.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28388e1_d28389e1_d28390e1\">To control the behavior of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> packing code in such circumstances, you can use the assignment setting <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wzv1665702719081.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wzv1665702719081.html\" title=\"Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code.\">$WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR</a> to set the behavior of all <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> String fields in your application. To set the behavior of <code class=\"ph codeph\">W</code> String fields in a specific entity, use the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"blo1665702710364.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/blo1665702710364.html\" title=\"Specify the character set used for String fields with the W packing code. If the database does not support Unicode, or it supports only Unicode BMP, use this setting to change its behavior. Valid values are Unicode, BMP, or Use Character Set.\">Wide Character Behavior</a> property of the entity interface.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28391e1_d28392e1_d28393e1\">The value of <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Wide Character Behavior</span> overrides the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR</span> setting.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"uir1665702875362__note_w7699ab1b5b5b9_w7700ab1b5b5_w7701ab1b5_w7702ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Setting the assignment setting or\n      property to use the character set, switches the W packing code to a C packing code, in which\n      case you must also set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span> assignment setting or\n        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Character Set</span> entity interface property.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uir1665702875362__topic_d18952e1_d18953e1_d18954e1_d18955e1_d18956e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355214e133\">\n                        \n U* Packing Code\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28397e1_d28398e1_d28399e1\">It is possible to store Unicode data in fields with a U* packing code by setting the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jpa1665702722765.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jpa1665702722765.html\" title=\"Set the data storage format of String fields with the U* packing code to XML or TRX.\">$META_IN_TRX</a> assignment setting to <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>. This causes the data to be stored in XML format, therefore, it can be used for holding Unicode characters.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uir1665702875362__topic_d18957e1_d18958e1_d18959e1_d18960e1_d18961e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d355214e155\">\n                        \n C Packing Code\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28403e1_d28404e1_d28405e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> packing code is used for characters in an installable character set. This can be specified using the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"udr1665702710295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/udr1665702710295.html\" title=\"Character set used for storing the entity in the database.\">Character Set</a> property of the entity interface, or the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fmh1665702657664.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmh1665702657664.html\" title=\"Set or return the value of $DEF_CHARSET, which defines the character set used for storing data in String fields with C packing code.\">$def_charset</a> (if the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Character Set</span> is <code class=\"ph codeph\">(default)</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uir1665702875362__p_d28406e1_d28407e1_d28408e1\">If the specified character set is Unicode, the <code class=\"ph codeph\">C</code> String fields are also used for Unicode characters.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/udi1665702731005.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Unicode</a><p>Unicode is an industry standard designed to allow text and symbols from all languages to be consistently represented and manipulated by computers.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xgd1665702875492.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Wide Character Packing Code (W)</a><p>The W (wide character) packing code is used for Unicode characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/otr1665702875565.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>TRX Character Packing Codes (U, VU, and SU)</a><p>The U, VU, and SU packing codes should be specified for any data that is to be stored in the Uniface transfer format (TRX). TRX has not been used since Uniface 8, so these packing codes are only available to ensure compatibility with older applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzj1665702875634.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Character Packing Code (C)</a><p>The C packing code is used for String data types.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532701\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532701\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Packing Codes for Unicode Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Packing Codes for Unicode By default, the W packing code is for Unicode characters. The U* packing code can also be used for holding Unicode characters. If the entity character set is Unicode, the C packing code can also be used for Unicode characters. Fields with data type String can be used for Unicode. If a string field is a Unifield, it can hold bold, italic, and underline characters. W Packing Code By default, if a string field uses the W packing code, it can contain any Unicode character. However, some databases support only Unicode BMP (Basic Multilingual Plane ), or do not support Unicode at all. To control the behavior of the W packing code in such circumstances, you can use the assignment setting $WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR to set the behavior of all W String fields in your application. To set the behavior of W String fields in a specific entity, use the Wide Character Behavior property of the entity interface. The value of Wide Character Behavior overrides the $WIDE_CHAR_BEHAVIOR setting. Note: Setting the assignment setting or property to use the character set, switches the W packing code to a C packing code, in which case you must also set the $DEF_CHARSET assignment setting or Character Set entity interface property. U* Packing Code It is possible to store Unicode data in fields with a U* packing code by setting the $META_IN_TRX assignment setting to 0 . This causes the data to be stored in XML format, therefore, it can be used for holding Unicode characters. C Packing Code The C packing code is used for characters in an installable character set. This can be specified using the Character Set property of the entity interface, or the $def_charset (if the Character Set is (default) . If the specified character set is Unicode, the C String fields are also used for Unicode characters. Related Links Unicode Unicode is an industry standard designed to allow text and symbols from all languages to be consistently represented and manipulated by computers. Wide Character Packing Code (W) The W (wide character) packing code is used for Unicode characters. TRX Character Packing Codes (U, VU, and SU) The U, VU, and SU packing codes should be specified for any data that is to be stored in the Uniface transfer format (TRX). TRX has not been used since Uniface 8, so these packing codes are only available to ensure compatibility with older applications. Character Packing Code (C) The C packing code is used for String data types. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}